trans-unit.source: Storage Analytics Logged Operations and Status Messages
trans-unit.target: Storage Analytics Logged Operations and Status Messages

trans-unit.source: This topic lists the storage service operations and status messages that are recorded by Storage Analytics.
trans-unit.target: This topic lists the storage service operations and status messages that are recorded by Storage Analytics.

trans-unit.source: The following table contains the status messages that are logged and reported in metrics data.
trans-unit.target: The following table contains the status messages that are logged and reported in metrics data.

trans-unit.source: A definition for each column is listed below:
trans-unit.target: A definition for each column is listed below:

trans-unit.source: <system>Status Message</system>: The status message for a request logged by Storage Analytics.
trans-unit.target: <system>Status Message</system>: The status message for a request logged by Storage Analytics.

trans-unit.source: This value is included in log entries and is the name of a column in each Metrics table.
trans-unit.target: This value is included in log entries and is the name of a column in each Metrics table.

trans-unit.source: <system>Description</system>: A description of the status message including HTTP verbs and status codes, if applicable.
trans-unit.target: <system>Description</system>: A description of the status message including HTTP verbs and status codes, if applicable.

trans-unit.source: <system>Billable</system>: A yes/no value that indicates whether or not the request is billable.
trans-unit.target: <system>Billable</system>: A yes/no value that indicates whether or not the request is billable.

trans-unit.source: For more information on billing in Azure Storage, see <externalLink><linkText>Understanding Azure Storage Billing - Bandwidth, Transactions, and Capacity</linkText><linkUri>http://blogs.msdn.com/b/windowsazurestorage/archive/2010/07/09/understanding-windows-azure-storage-billing-bandwidth-transactions-and-capacity.aspx</linkUri></externalLink>.
trans-unit.target: For more information on billing in Azure Storage, see <externalLink><linkText>Understanding Azure Storage Billing - Bandwidth, Transactions, and Capacity</linkText><linkUri>http://blogs.msdn.com/b/windowsazurestorage/archive/2010/07/09/understanding-windows-azure-storage-billing-bandwidth-transactions-and-capacity.aspx</linkUri></externalLink>.

trans-unit.source: <system>Availability</system>: A yes/no value that indicates whether or not the request is included in the availability calculation for a storage service or a specific API operation.
trans-unit.target: <system>Availability</system>: A yes/no value that indicates whether or not the request is included in the availability calculation for a storage service or a specific API operation.

trans-unit.source: All unexpected errors result in reduced availability for the storage service or the specified API operation.
trans-unit.target: All unexpected errors result in reduced availability for the storage service or the specified API operation.
